The paper proposes a novel approach for image completion, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The approach involves using autoregressive models and low-rank minimization, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves numerical optimization, which falls under cs.MM (Mathematical Software). Additionally, the paper involves signal processing techniques such as autoregressive models, which fall under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves numerical methods for solving optimization problems, which fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
